item.title: EGUI not found?
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

A.) The defined path for EGUI does not match the actual path for EGUI
B.) EGUI doesn’t exist.

Solutions:
A.) Compare the code inside your batch file to the actual directory of the class file your trying to run.
B.) If EGUI doesn’t exist, change the code in your batch file to load client class.
